Academic.desc:
This student organization is not for profit and its purpose shall be to:
Allow the undergraduate students of Eleanor Roosevelt College to showcase their research projects;
Motivate ERC students to involve themselves in the many research opportunities available to them on campus and beyond;
Create an environment in ERC that encourages open collaboration between students and staff;
Educate journal staffers on the process of building a professional research magazine;
Publicize ERC-exclusive programs that permit research opportunities, including Break-Away Global Service (BAGS), Making of the Modern World (MMW) and the Undergraduate Research Conference (URC);
Bring together students and faculty to help students explore career options and research projects.

To unite students who want to compete in the William Lowell Putnam Mathematical Competition;
To actively prepare ourselves and each other to perform admirably in the aforementioned competition;
To improve our mathematical problem solving skills.

Panhellenic.desc:
PURPOSE OF THE ORDER OF OMEGA

To recognize those fraternity men and women who have attained a high standard of leadership in interfraternity activities, to encourage them to continue along this line, and to inspire others to strive for similar conspicuous attainment;
To bring together outstanding fraternity men and women to create an organization which will help to mold the sentiment of the institution on questions of local and intercollegiate fraternity affairs.

Pre-Professional.desc:
TESC wants to develop engineers who exhibit leadership through excellence in all aspects of life:
- Prepare students for, and connect them with, professional opportunities;
- Coordinate, and collaborate with, engineering student organizations;
- Create and maintain a vibrant community for engineering students; and
- Champion engineering and engineers in the school, community, and beyond.
